{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ebb6332b-ccf1-4d54-9964-9c8b0150c128","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest adapter.** That's the breaking change.\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK bundled both the new **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** runner *and* the legacy VSTest adapter, so `vstest.console` still worked. In 4.x, the VSTest adapter is no longer included — `vstest.console` finds no tests because there's nothing for it to discover through.\n\n### Fix: switch your CI from `vstest.console` to `dotnet test`\n\nModern `dotnet test` (**.NET SDK 8.0.400+**) integrates with Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly. Replace:\n\n```bash\n# ❌ Old (no longer works)\nvstest.console TestProject.dll\n\n# ✅ New\ndotnet test\n```\n\nIf you're on an older .NET SDK that doesn't yet bridge `dotnet test` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you can also run the test binary directly:\n\n```bash\n# The compiled test project IS the test runner now\n./bin/Release/net8.0/TestProject.exe\n```\n\nNo project file changes needed — your `.csproj` is already correct.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"eda3f209-6737-412f-83a2-355acf6b056b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the SDK uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new test platform) by default instead of the legacy VSTest platform. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed or is no longer included by default.\n\nThe key change: **MSTest.Sdk/3.4+** (or specifically around version 3.x) started defaulting to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. But with MSTest.Sdk/4.x, the VSTest adapter/compatibility bridge is no longer included, so `vstest.console` can't discover tests anymore.\n\n\nIn version 3.x, both the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform and the VSTest adapter shipped together, but 4.x removed the VSTest adapter entirely, leaving Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the sole supported runner. This means `vstest.console` can no longer find or run tests. The solution is to migrate your CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` instead, which natively supports the new platform, or run the test binary directly with `dotnet exec`. NET SDK 8.0.4xx+), so the practical fix is to switch from `vstest.console` to `dotnet test` in CI, or invoke the test executable directly.","outputTokens":834,"requestId":"1BD2:2912D8:C22E6E:DB239E:6A03F2AD"},"id":"d7caf58a-117b-4a89-ae52-0f7bb7d72e45","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:40:46.562Z","parentId":"2233cbe6-13f9-4311-83d7-bf5a3bd2d2d8"}
